ported dynamic generation for native runtime. But maybe cglib's Preserve allows for dynamic class loading? I wonder if existing tests using ReflectUtils.defineClass would fail in this context. Let's assume cglib could run successfully.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Planning coverage for call sites**\\n\\nI need to ensure we have coverage for specific call sites. For instance, Class.forName requires referencing the Enhancer class or static helper to get covered. Functions like getDeclaredConstructors in generateClass are covered by Enhancer.createClass/create. Additionally, getDeclaredMethod in getCallbacksSetter needs coverage as well. I'll design a test file named EnhancerTest in the package cglib.cglib_nodep. It should be a public top class that avoids direct reflection and primarily uses the public API methods like createClass and registerStaticCallbacks. If we need instantiation, we can use a Factory.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_TJTloKrf2Nthjpsb7BWgG3s7|fc_006f35700f21a5690169ef5fb0efbc8191abc558996588daeb", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find /home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/source_context/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2 -maxdepth 4 -type d | head -40 && rg -n \"class TestEnhancer|Enhancer\" /home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/local_repositories/source_context/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2 -g '*.java' | head -80", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1870, "output": 2028, "cacheRead": 37888, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41786, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777295253023, "responseId": "resp_006f35700f21a5690169ef5f959cec819188a289a043d55539"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_TJTloKrf2Nthjpsb7BWgG3s7|fc_006f35700f21a5690169ef5fb0efbc8191abc558996588daeb", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/home/vjovanov/c/f